<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

{{> header}}

<body>
    {{> navbar}}

    <header>
        <div class="header-content">
            <div class="header-content-inner">
                <h1 style="font-size: 65px;">Donate</h1>
                <p>Support our peace building and community empowerment work</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <section id="volunteering-intro">
        <div class="container text-justify">
            <div class="row">
                <h2 class="text-center" style="font-weight: 600;">Donate now, support the work of YPB in West Africa and give people in fragile and conflict affected areas
                    a chance!!</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <p id="firstText" class="text-justify">
                    Almost a quarter of the world’s population lives in poverty. They are the most vulnerable to natural disasters, war and violence.
                    YPB wants everybody to have the chance to live a safe and worthy life, with access to healthcare, education
                    and economic opportunities. With over 15 years of experience, YPB has a leading role in innovative and
                    effective forms of development in West Africa.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="volunteering-join">
        <div class="container text-justify">
            <div class="row">
                <h3>Promoting Tourism</h3>
                <p>Young Peace Brigades creates opportunities for West Africa’s poorest, most vulnerable and excluded people.
                    Regardless of race or religion, YPB provides African citizens and Youths with an opportunity to make
                    their voices heard.
                </p>

                <p>Join 0ver 2,000 volunteers across West Africa who believe we can build flourishing communities together,
                    even in the most fragile or conflict-ridden areas.</p>

                <p>In flourishing communities people share values, interests and a common purpose. Flourishing communities create
                    space where people can live with dignity, safely, have the freedom to speak out and have access to quality
                    and affordable basic services, such as healthcare.</p>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <h3>Medical Supplies Needed</h3>
                <div id="medications" class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                    <h4>Medications</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li> Deworming tablets/syrup</li>
                        <li> Simple emollient</li>
                        <li> Antiseptic cream</li>
                        <li> Antihistamine cream</li>
                        <li> Steroid cream e.g. hydrocortisone</li>
                        <li> Clotrimazole pessaries</li>
                        <li> Clotrimazole cream</li>
                        <li> Antiemetic tablets</li>
                        <li> Antibiotics (currently required: Metronidazole, Flucloxacillin, Benzyl penicillin, Penicillin V,
                        </li>
                        Clindamycin, Trimethoprim, Coamoxiclav, Nitrofurantoin, Ceftriaxone )
                        <li> syrup/tablets/injection.</li>
                        <li> Antibiotic ear & eye drops e.g. gentisone HC, ofloxacin, Fusidic acid</li>
                        <li> Small supply of antihypertensives eg Enalapril, Amlodipine, HCTZ </li>
                        <li> Small supply of Metformin </li>
                        <li> Local anaesthetic e.g. lignocaine, lidocaine</li>
                        <li> Condoms (male and female) </li>
                        <li> Epinephrine autoinjector e.g. EpiPen</li>
                        <li> Tetanus vaccinations</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="equipment" class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                    <h4>Equipment</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li> urine dipstick tests</li>
                        <li> pregnancy tests</li>
                        <li> cotton wool pads</li>
                        <li> clinical disinfectant wipes</li>
                        <li> sterile gloves of a range of sizes</li>
                        <li> small alcohol wipes/pads</li>
                        <li> Glucose monitoring strips   </li>
                        <li> Incontinence pads</li>
                        <li> Small bandage</li>
                        <li> Tegaderm dressings (or similar) of all sizes</li>
                        <li> Non-adherent dressings of all sizes</li>
                        <li> Catheter bag</li>
                        <li> Vaginal speculums</li>
                        <li> Cotton-tipped swabs</li>
                        <li> Sterile water</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <h3>Wishlist</h3>
                <div id="medications" class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                    <h4>Medications</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Steroid injections</li>
                        <li>Fluconazole tablets</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="equipment" class="col-md-6 col-sm-12">
                    <h4>Equipment</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Chlamydia tests</li>
                        <li>Helicobacter pylori testing kits</li>
                        <li>Contraception - injection e.g. depo-provera, pill (COCP & POP)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>


    <section id="volunteering-intro">
        <div class="container text-justify">
            <div class="row">
                <h2 class="text-center" style="font-weight: 600;">Support African Youth Peace Advocacy</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <p id="firstText" class="text-justify">
                    The adoption of UN Security Council resolution 2250 on Youth, Peace and Security was a major achievement for the youth movement
                    for peace. But this is not enough! Now we need to make sure that the Resolution is being implemented
                    locally, and we need to advocate for it! UNOY Peacebuilders are planning to set up a specific Africa
                    Youth Advocacy Team.
                </p>

                <p id="firstText" class="text-justify">
                    Support the African Peace Advocacy of United Network of Young Peacebuilders and its members. Invest in young people as change
                    agents. Every small contribution counts. More instructions on how to donate <a href="http://unoy.org/en/african-youth- peace-advocacy/">here</a>.
                    Thank you!!
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    {{> footer}}

</body>

</html>